# Civs + RPG — project scope

## What we are building

Two custom plugins for one territorial RPG server (Paper 26.1.2, Java 25):

| Plugin | Path | Role |
|--------|------|------|
| **Civs Custom** | `../Civs-1.11.6/` | World engine: towns, regions, combat, spells, economy infra, internal skills, future AH/mobs/turrets |
| **RPG Server** | `rpg-server-plugin/` | Orchestration: quests, archetypes, perks, LuckPerms gates, softdepend hooks |

**Product decision:** Civs `TutorialManager` = onboarding; RPG quests = mid/endgame parallel paths (option 2). Unify later (Sprint 4+).

## Server stack (19 plugins — use softdepend, do not reimplement)

**Integrate:** Civs, AuraSkills, ChestShop, Essentials, InteractiveBooks, LuckPerms, PlaceholderAPI, Vault, VeinMiner (optional).

**Skip:** MiniMOTD, ChestSort, ChunkLoader, Chunky, GSit, EssentialsChat, NBTAPI, prism.

**Reference only** (`../reference-plugins/`): KingdomX, Heroes, BeautyQuests, MythicMobs, Citizens, AuctionHouse — study patterns; implement natively in Civs/RPG when no server plugin exists.

## Ownership (never violate)

| Domain | Owner |
|--------|-------|
| Player skill XP & combat stats | **AuraSkills** |
| Territorial skills, shop discounts, building XP | **Civs internal** (`GainExpEvent`) |
| Towns, regions, siege, town bank | **Civs** |
| Player shops | **ChestShop** |
| Quest step state | **RPG YAML only** — never duplicate XP ledger |
| Money | **Vault** (Essentials provider) |
| Unlocks | **LuckPerms** |

## What NOT to do

- Do **not** install reference plugins (KingdomX, BeautyQuests, MythicMobs, etc.) on the server.
- Do **not** replace AuraSkills with Civs skills for player progression.
- Do **not** build native Civs chest shop while ChestShop is on server.
- Do **not** copy GPL/CC-BY-ND reference code verbatim — reimplement patterns.
- Do **not** duplicate quest engines (BeautyQuests) — extend RPG `ObjectiveTypeRegistry`.
- Do **not** call Civs managers for writes from RPG — use events + public APIs + reward delegation.
- Do **not** commit `.cursor/` IDE state except `skills/` and `rules/`.

